            short: "AI monitoring of supplier health indicators — financial stability, delivery performance, news sentiment, and geopolitical risk.",
            detail: "AI can monitor supplier risk signals at a breadth and speed that manual approaches can’t match. Particularly valuable for critical tier-1 and tier-2 suppliers.",
            riskNote: "A missed supplier risk signal can result in supply disruption. AI monitoring improves coverage but requires clear escalation workflows." }
        ]
      },
      {
        id: "09", title: "Knowledge & Content Ops",
        items: [
          { name: "Internal Knowledge Base Management", level: "transformative", isNew: true, risk: "reversible",
            short: "AI-powered search and answer generation across internal documentation, replacing manual knowledge hunting.",
            detail: "The amount of time employees spend searching for internal information is staggering. AI that can surface relevant answers from across wikis, docs, and Slack is a clear productivity win.",
            riskNote: "A wrong answer wastes time. An outdated answer causes rework. Easy to correct and the cost of errors is low relative to the time saved." },
          { name: "Content Generation & Editing", level: "transformative", isNew: false, risk: "moderate",
            short: "AI that drafts, edits, and formats business content — reports, proposals, presentations, communications — from prompts or templates.",
            detail: "This is the category most people experience first. AI dramatically accelerates content production. The quality ceiling depends on the operator’s ability to prompt and edit.",
            riskNote: "Published content with errors, inappropriate tone, or incorrect claims creates reputational risk. Human review and approval workflows are required for external content." },
          { name: "Translation & Localisation", level: "high", isNew: false, risk: "moderate",
            short: "AI translation of business content, documentation, and communications across languages with context-aware localisation.",
            detail: "AI translation quality has improved dramatically. For internal communications and documentation, AI translation is often good enough to deploy without professional review.",
            riskNote: "Translation errors in customer-facing or legal content create reputational and compliance risk. Professional review for high-stakes content remains necessary." },
          { name: "Meeting Summarisation & Action Items", level: "high", isNew: false, risk: "reversible",
            short: "AI that transcribes meetings, generates structured summaries, and extracts action items with ownership and deadlines.",
            detail: "One of the fastest-adoption AI tools in enterprise. Meeting notes go from ‘someone takes notes’ to ‘everyone gets a searchable summary within minutes’.",
            riskNote: "A missed or misattributed action item creates follow-up friction. Participants can correct the record easily. Low lasting impact." }
        ]
      },
      {
        id: "10", title: "Facilities & Physical Ops",
        items: [
          { name: "Predictive Maintenance", level: "high", isNew: false, risk: "moderate",
            short: "AI that predicts equipment failures from sensor data and usage patterns, enabling proactive maintenance scheduling.",
            detail: "Predictive maintenance is one of the most proven AI use cases in facilities and manufacturing. Moving from scheduled to predictive maintenance reduces both downtime and unnecessary servicing.",
            riskNote: "A missed failure prediction results in unplanned downtime. An over-prediction results in unnecessary maintenance costs. Both are meaningful but manageable." },
          { name: "Space & Occupancy Optimisation", level: "medium", isNew: false, risk: "reversible",
            short: "AI analysis of occupancy data to optimise space utilisation, desk allocation, and facilities planning.",
            detail: "With hybrid work patterns, space utilisation data is more important and more variable. AI can model occupancy patterns and recommend space configurations.",
            riskNote: "A bad space recommendation creates employee inconvenience. Easy to reverse and test alternatives." },
          { name: "Energy Management", level: "medium", isNew: false, risk: "reversible",
            short: "AI-controlled HVAC, lighting, and energy systems that optimise for cost and comfort based on occupancy and conditions.",
            detail: "AI energy management can reduce facility energy costs by 15-30% through real-time optimisation. The ROI is well-established in commercial buildings.",
            riskNote: "Uncomfortable temperature or lighting conditions are noticeable and quickly correctable. Low lasting impact." }
        ]
      }
    ],
    principles: [
      { num: "01", title: "Start Where <em>Risk Is Low</em>", desc: "Your first AI ops deployment should be in a category where errors are reversible and low-cost. Build confidence before moving to critical systems.",
        focus: ["Process documentation & SOPs", "IT helpdesk triage", "Internal knowledge base", "Meeting summarisation"] },
      { num: "02", title: "Human-in-the-Loop Is <em>Not Optional</em> for Critical Systems", desc: "Any category with critical consequence of failure requires human sign-off regardless of how good the AI is. This is not a temporary limitation.",
        focus: ["Resume screening & hiring", "Financial reporting & forecasts", "Contract review", "Access & identity management"] },
      { num: "03", title: "The AI Does the <em>First Draft</em>", desc: "For moderate-risk categories, the best pattern is AI generating the first version and a human reviewing, editing, and approving. This captures most of the time savings while maintaining quality.",
        focus: ["Performance reviews", "Budget variance reports", "Onboarding workflows", "Content generation"] },
      { num: "04", title: "Monitor the <em>AI’s Work</em>, Not Just the Output", desc: "Once AI handles a process, you need visibility into how it’s performing — not just whether the final output looks right. Build monitoring from day one.",
        focus: ["QA review of AI support interactions", "Audit trails for automated decisions", "Anomaly detection on AI outputs", "Regular accuracy reviews"] },
      { num: "05", title: "Combine Categories for <em>Compound Impact</em>", desc: "The biggest gains come from connecting AI across categories — not deploying it in isolation. Process mining that feeds automation design that feeds knowledge management.",
        focus: ["Process mining → workflow automation", "Support triage → knowledge base updates", "Invoice processing → spend analysis", "Demand forecasting → inventory management"] },
      { num: "06", title: "Disruption Level Is Not <em>Priority Level</em>", desc: "The most transformative categories are not necessarily where you should start. Priority = disruption level × relevance to your business ÷ consequence of failure.",
        focus: ["Map your current pain points first", "Score by operational impact, not hype", "Factor in your team’s readiness", "Build a phased roadmap, not a big bang"] }
    ]
  };

  var activeFilter = 'all';
  var container = document.getElementById('ops-sections-container');
  var principlesGrid = document.getElementById('ops-principles-grid');
  var overlay = document.getElementById('ops-modal-overlay');

  function capitalize(s) { return s.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + s.slice(1); }
  function pad2(n) { var s = String(n); return s.length < 2 ? '0' + s : s; }

  function renderSections() {
    var html = '';
    DATA.sections.forEach(function(section) {
      html += '<div class="op-ops-section" data-animate="fade-up">';
      html += '<div class="op-ops-section-header">';
      html += '<span class="op-mono op-ops-section-num">CAT_' + section.id + '</span>';
      html += '<h2 class="op-ops-section-title">' + section.title + '</h2>';
      html += '</div>';
      html += '<div class="op-ops-cards-grid" data-animate-stagger>';
      section.items.forEach(function(item, idx) {
        var hidden = '';
        if (activeFilter === 'new' && !item.isNew) hidden = ' hidden';
        else if (activeFilter !== 'all' && activeFilter !== 'new' && item.level !== activeFilter) hidden = ' hidden';

        var code = 'OP_' + section.id + '_' + pad2(idx + 1);
        html += '<div class="op-ops-card' + hidden + '" data-section="' + section.id + '" data-idx="' + idx + '" data-animate="fade-up">';
        html += '<header class="op-ops-card-head">';
        html += '<span class="op-pulse-dot"></span>';
        html += '<span class="op-mono op-ops-card-code">' + code + '</span>';
        html += '<span class="op-mono op-ops-card-tag">' + (item.isNew ? 'NEW' : capitalize(item.level).toUpperCase()) + '</span>';
        html += '</header>';
        html += '<div class="op-ops-card-body">';
        html += '<h3 class="op-ops-card-name">' + item.name + '</h3>';
        html += '<div class="op-ops-card-rule"></div>';
        html += '<div class="op-ops-card-pills">';
        html += '<span class="op-ops-level-pill level-' + item.level + '">' + capitalize(item.level) + '</span>';
        html += '<span class="op-ops-risk-pill risk-' + item.risk + '">' + capitalize(item.risk) + ' Risk</span>';
        if (item.isNew) html += '<span class="op-ops-new-pill">NEW</span>';
        html += '</div>';
        html += '<p class="op-ops-card-summary">' + item.short + '</p>';
        html += '<p class="op-ops-card-expand">VIEW DETAILS →</p>';
        html += '</div>';
        html += '</div>';
      });
      html += '</div></div>';
    });
    container.innerHTML = html;
    observeNewElements();
  }

  function renderPrinciples() {
    var html = '';
    DATA.principles.forEach(function(p) {
      html += '<div class="op-ops-principle-card" data-animate="fade-up">';
      html += '<header class="op-ops-principle-head">';
      html += '<span class="op-pulse-dot"></span>';
      html += '<span class="op-mono op-ops-principle-num">PRINCIPLE_' + p.num + '</span>';
      html += '<span class="op-mono op-ops-principle-tag">CROSS_CUTTING</span>';
      html += '</header>';
      html += '<div class="op-ops-principle-body">';
      html += '<h3 class="op-ops-principle-title">' + p.title + '</h3>';
      html += '<div class="op-ops-principle-rule"></div>';
      html += '<p class="op-ops-principle-desc">' + p.desc + '</p>';
      html += '<span class="op-mono op-ops-principle-focus-label">FOCUS AREAS</span>';
      html += '<ul class="op-ops-principle-focus-list">';
      p.focus.forEach(function(f) {
        html += '<li>' + f + '</li>';
      });
      html += '</ul>';
      html += '</div>';
      html += '</div>';
    });
    principlesGrid.innerHTML = html;
    observeNewElements();
  }

  function setFilter(filter) {
    activeFilter = filter;
    document.querySelectorAll('.op-ops-filter-btn').forEach(function(btn) {
      btn.classList.toggle('active', btn.getAttribute('data-filter') === filter);
    });
    document.querySelectorAll('.op-ops-legend-item').forEach(function(btn) {
      btn.classList.toggle('active', btn.getAttribute('data-filter') === filter);
    });
    renderSections();
  }

  function openModal(sectionId, idx) {
    var section = DATA.sections.find(function(s) { return s.id === sectionId; });
    if (!section) return;
    var item = section.items[idx];
    if (!item) return;

    document.getElementById('ops-modal-section-label').textContent = section.title.toUpperCase();
    document.getElementById('ops-modal-title').textContent = item.name;
    document.getElementById('ops-modal-short').textContent = item.short;
    document.getElementById('ops-modal-detail').textContent = item.detail;
    document.getElementById('ops-modal-risk-text').textContent = item.riskNote;

    var levelBadge = document.getElementById('ops-modal-level-badge');
    levelBadge.textContent = capitalize(item.level);
    levelBadge.className = 'op-ops-level-pill level-' + item.level;

    var riskBadge = document.getElementById('ops-modal-risk-badge');
    riskBadge.textContent = capitalize(item.risk) + ' Risk';
    riskBadge.className = 'op-ops-risk-pill risk-' + item.risk;

    var newTag = document.getElementById('ops-modal-new-tag');
    if (item.isNew) {
      newTag.innerHTML = '<span class="op-ops-new-pill">NEW</span>';
    } else {
      newTag.innerHTML = '';
    }

    overlay.classList.add('open');
    document.body.style.overflow = 'hidden';
  }

  function closeModal() {
    overlay.classList.remove('open');
    document.body.style.overflow = '';
  }

  function observeNewElements() {
    var obs = new IntersectionObserver(function(entries) {
      entries.forEach(function(entry) {
        if (entry.isIntersecting) {
          entry.target.classList.add('is-visible');
        }
      });
    }, { rootMargin: '0px 0px -80px 0px', threshold: 0.1 });

    document.querySelectorAll('[data-animate]:not(.is-visible)').forEach(function(el) {
      obs.observe(el);
    });
    document.querySelectorAll('[data-animate-stagger]:not(.is-visible)').forEach(function(el) {
      obs.observe(el);
    });
  }

  // Event delegation
  document.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
    var filterBtn = e.target.closest('.op-ops-filter-btn');
    if (filterBtn) {
      setFilter(filterBtn.getAttribute('data-filter'));
      return;
    }
    var legendBtn = e.target.closest('.op-ops-legend-item');
    if (legendBtn) {
      setFilter(legendBtn.getAttribute('data-filter'));
      return;
    }
    var card = e.target.closest('.op-ops-card');
    if (card) {
      openModal(card.getAttribute('data-section'), parseInt(card.getAttribute('data-idx')));
      return;
    }
    if (e.target.closest('#ops-modal-close')) {
      closeModal();
      return;
    }
    if (e.target === overlay) {
      closeModal();
      return;
    }
  });

  document.addEventListener('keydown', function(e) {
    if (e.key === 'Escape') closeModal();
  });

  // Initial render
  renderSections();
  renderPrinciples();
})();
</script>
